1
00:00:10,541 --> 00:00:13,041
- ( theme music playing )

2
00:02:06,416 --> 00:02:08,291
- ( tires squeal, engine revs )

3
00:02:17,666 --> 00:02:20,041
- ( pop music playing )

4
00:02:42,666 --> 00:02:44,958
- YOU DIDN'T HIT THAT CORNER
TIGHT ENOUGH, MAKO.

5
00:02:45,041 --> 00:02:46,041
- ( gasps )

6
00:02:46,125 --> 00:02:47,666
- I'D EXPECT A TIGHTER
LINE FROM YOU.

7
00:02:47,750 --> 00:02:49,250
I KNOW YOU'RE
BETTER THAN THAT.

8
00:02:49,333 --> 00:02:51,250
YOU'RE OFF BY LIKE
FIVE INCHES.

9
00:02:51,333 --> 00:02:53,291
- YEAH, I KNOW.

10
00:02:57,458 --> 00:02:58,875
- HMM?

11
00:02:58,958 --> 00:03:00,750
HEY, LOOK.
SOMEONE'S COMING DOWN THE PASS.

12
00:03:07,583 --> 00:03:09,458
MAKO'S SIL-EIGHTY!
SHE ROCKS THIS PASS.

13
00:03:09,541 --> 00:03:11,000
- SO FREAKING COOL.

14
00:03:11,083 --> 00:03:13,666
- NOTHING MOVES SWEETER
THAN USUI'S FASTEST.

15
00:03:13,750 --> 00:03:15,375
THAT'S WHY THEY'RE CALLED
"IMPACT BLUE."

16
00:03:26,708 --> 00:03:30,166
- Sayuki:
OH, YOU SUCK TONIGHT!

17
00:03:30,250 --> 00:03:32,291
THIS CRAP DRIVING'S
NOT LIKE YOU, MAKO.

18
00:03:32,375 --> 00:03:35,583
CONCENTRATE. WHAT'S GOING ON
IN THAT HEAD OF YOURS, HUH? 

19
00:03:59,833 --> 00:04:01,583
Sayuki: SO THAT'S HOW
IT ALL WENT DOWN.

20
00:04:01,666 --> 00:04:03,083
I WAS WONDERING.

21
00:04:03,166 --> 00:04:04,833
AND I CAN'T BELIEVE
THAT YOU GOT DUMPED

22
00:04:04,916 --> 00:04:07,291
BY IKETANI. YOU'RE SO WAY
OUT OF HIS LEAGUE ANYWAY.

23
00:04:07,375 --> 00:04:09,333
- I KNOW.

24
00:04:09,416 --> 00:04:11,041
YOU'VE SAID THAT BEFORE,
BUT STILL.

25
00:04:11,125 --> 00:04:13,333
- IT'S COMING TOGETHER
FOR ME NOW.

26
00:04:13,416 --> 00:04:15,583
NO WONDER YOU'VE BEEN
DRIVING LIKE A LOOSE CANNON.

27
00:04:15,666 --> 00:04:18,333
YOU'RE THE TYPE OF PERSON
WHO'S DRIVING MIRRORS

28
00:04:18,416 --> 00:04:21,125
EXACTLY HOW YOU'RE FEELING.

29
00:04:21,208 --> 00:04:23,250
RACING WITH YOUR EMOTIONS,
THAT'S YOUR STYLE.

30
00:04:47,291 --> 00:04:48,500
- Yuuichi:
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO NOW?!

31
00:04:48,583 --> 00:04:50,375
- ( gasps )
- BEING IN LOVE MEANS

32
00:04:50,458 --> 00:04:52,458
YOU ACCEPT EVERYTHING 
ABOUT THE OTHER PERSON

33
00:04:52,541 --> 00:04:55,250
THE WAY THEY ARE. I MEAN,
THAT'S WHAT LOVE'S ALL ABOUT.

34
00:04:55,333 --> 00:04:57,250
- ( stammers )

35
00:04:57,333 --> 00:04:59,041
- YOU WON'T KNOW IF
SHE'S WAITING FOR YOU OR NOT

36
00:04:59,125 --> 00:05:01,541
TILL YOU GO.
NOW GET OUT OF HERE RIGHT NOW

37
00:05:01,625 --> 00:05:04,166
OR YOU'RE FIRED.
- ( groans )

38
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:23,416
-  MEET ME AT 8:00
AT THE KAMAMESHI BILLBOARD

39
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:25,625
WHERE WE MET.
I'LL BE THERE.

40
00:05:27,791 --> 00:05:30,166
- Iketani:
BOSS IS RIGHT.  I'M SO STUPID.

41
00:05:30,250 --> 00:05:32,708
SHE WAS ALWAYS
STRAIGHT UP WITH ME.

42
00:05:32,791 --> 00:05:34,416
BUT I COULDN'T DO IT BACK.

43
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:36,625
I'M SUCH A JACKASS.

44
00:05:39,333 --> 00:05:41,833
- MY FEET ARE KILLING ME.

45
00:05:41,916 --> 00:05:43,625
I HATE HEELS.

46
00:05:46,791 --> 00:05:48,833
- OH, PLEASE, PLEASE.

47
00:05:48,916 --> 00:05:51,416
JUST ONE MORE CHANCE.

48
00:05:51,500 --> 00:05:52,833
( gasps )

49
00:05:52,916 --> 00:05:54,833
NO!  THERE'S AN ACCIDENT?

50
00:05:54,916 --> 00:05:56,416
- ( crying )

51
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:59,333
I'M NEVER WEARING
HIGH HEELS AGAIN.

52
00:06:00,666 --> 00:06:02,416
- ( engine starts )

53
00:06:04,541 --> 00:06:06,333
- ( tires screech )

54
00:06:36,958 --> 00:06:39,708
- I CAN'T FATHOM HOW ANYONE
WOULD WANT TO BREAK UP WITH YOU.

55
00:06:39,791 --> 00:06:41,375
YOU'RE AWESOME.
AND HE LOOKED LIKE

56
00:06:41,458 --> 00:06:44,000
HE WAS OVER THE MOON
CRAZY FOR YOU TOO.

57
00:06:44,083 --> 00:06:46,000
BUT I GUESS THAT'S
GUYS FOR YOU.

58
00:06:46,083 --> 00:06:48,958
MAYBE YOU TWO GOT
YOUR MEETING TIMES MIXED UP?

59
00:06:49,041 --> 00:06:51,666
- I THOUGHT ABOUT THAT, SO I
STAYED THERE WAITING FOR HIM.

60
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:53,416
I WAS THERE FOREVER AFTER
WE WERE SUPPOSED TO MEET,

61
00:06:53,500 --> 00:06:55,000
BUT NOTHING.

62
00:06:55,083 --> 00:06:57,416
- AND THE JERK NEVER
EVEN BOTHERED TO CALL YOU?

63
00:06:59,791 --> 00:07:01,916
SO WHY DON'T YOU
JUST CALL HIM?

64
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:04,333
- I COULDN'T BE THAT FORWARD.
YOU KNOW THAT.

65
00:07:04,416 --> 00:07:07,166
BESIDES, AFTER WAITING THERE
FOR THREE EXTRA HOURS,

66
00:07:07,250 --> 00:07:08,708
I WAS HUMILIATED.

67
00:07:08,791 --> 00:07:10,416
AND THE FACT THAT
HE HASN'T EVEN BOTHERED

68
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:12,250
TO CALL ME AFTER THAT NIGHT?

69
00:07:12,333 --> 00:07:15,458
I'M PRETTY SURE THAT MEANS
HE'S NOT INTERESTED.

70
00:07:15,541 --> 00:07:17,083
- ( sighs )

71
00:07:17,166 --> 00:07:18,916
SOUNDS LIKE YOU WERE
REALLY STOKED OVER THIS GUY.

72
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:20,500
THAT REALLY SUCKS.

73
00:07:20,583 --> 00:07:21,833
STOKED ENOUGH THAT IT 
JACKED WITH HOW YOU'RE

74
00:07:21,916 --> 00:07:23,666
HANDLING YOURSELF
BEHIND THE WHEEL.

75
00:07:23,750 --> 00:07:27,750
- YEAH.  AND I WAS READY TO
HAND IT ALL OVER TO HIM.

76
00:07:27,833 --> 00:07:30,666
- HUH?  HAND WHAT?

77
00:07:32,416 --> 00:07:33,333
- ME.

78
00:07:33,416 --> 00:07:36,416
- ( coughing )

79
00:07:36,500 --> 00:07:39,958
I CAN'T TELL IF YOU'RE
SOME NAIVE LITTLE GIRL

80
00:07:40,041 --> 00:07:41,708
OR A WALKING SET OF
BRASS BALLS.

81
00:07:41,791 --> 00:07:43,208
I REALLY CAN'T.

82
00:07:43,291 --> 00:07:44,708
YOU GOTTA FILL ME IN.

83
00:07:44,791 --> 00:07:46,791
WHAT'S SO SPECIAL
ABOUT THIS GUY ANYWAY?

84
00:07:51,041 --> 00:07:53,541
- IT'S HARD TO EXPLAIN.

85
00:07:53,625 --> 00:07:55,125
HE'S SINCERE AND GENTLE.

86
00:07:55,208 --> 00:07:58,583
HE WAS NEVER PUSHY.

87
00:07:58,666 --> 00:08:01,541
WHENEVER WE STARTED
TALKING ABOUT CARS,

88
00:08:01,625 --> 00:08:03,125
TIMES JUST SOARED BY.

89
00:08:03,208 --> 00:08:05,541
WE MUST HAVE REALLY
GOTTEN INTO IT.

90
00:08:05,625 --> 00:08:07,958
THAT WAS JUST PART OF
THE MAGIC, I GUESS.

91
00:08:09,666 --> 00:08:12,000
- ( cellphone ringing )

92
00:08:12,083 --> 00:08:14,166
- THIS IS SAYUKI.

93
00:08:14,250 --> 00:08:16,000
SHINGO, LONG TIME NO TALK.

94
00:08:16,083 --> 00:08:18,125
HOW'S THE BIG BAD WORLD
BEEN TREATING YOU LATELY?

95
00:08:18,208 --> 00:08:20,416
- JUST FINE.

96
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:23,208
BUT THIS ISN'T A SOCIAL CALL.

97
00:08:23,291 --> 00:08:25,000
- WHAT?  ARE YOU SERIOUS?

98
00:08:25,083 --> 00:08:27,375
WHAT'S THE LAN-EVO SQUAD
DOING IN MYOGI?

99
00:08:34,333 --> 00:08:36,583
- I'M WONDERING IF THE NEWS
HAD REACHED YOU YET.

100
00:08:36,666 --> 00:08:39,000
LAN-EVO'S WITH TOCHIGI PLATES
SHOWED IN MYOGI

101
00:08:39,083 --> 00:08:41,000
NOT TOO LONG AGO.

102
00:08:41,083 --> 00:08:42,833
- THAT'S OKAY.

103
00:08:42,916 --> 00:08:47,000
- I HEAR THE NIGHT KIDS
LOST THEIR ASSES TO THEM TOO.

104
00:08:47,083 --> 00:08:49,041
COURSE IT WAS THAT IDIOT,
TAKESHI.

105
00:08:49,125 --> 00:08:51,375
HAD TO LOSE TO THOSE SPEED
MONKEYS ON OUR HOME TURF.

106
00:08:54,125 --> 00:08:56,041
- I KNOW WHO
THESE GUYS ARE.

107
00:08:56,125 --> 00:08:59,041
A FELLOW NAMED KYOICHI SUDO
IS THEIR LEADER.

108
00:08:59,125 --> 00:09:00,875
HE'S AN EXCELLENT RACER
WHO HAILS FROM

109
00:09:00,958 --> 00:09:02,500
THE NIKKO IROHAZAKA COURSE.

110
00:09:02,583 --> 00:09:03,791
- ( gasps )

111
00:09:03,875 --> 00:09:07,125
- I KNOW YOU'RE HERE NOW,
KYOICHI.

112
00:09:07,208 --> 00:09:10,250
THE ONLY QUESTION IS WHAT DO
YOU HAVE UP YOUR SLEEVE?

113
00:09:16,708 --> 00:09:18,583
- WE SHOULD DO THIS
MORE OFTEN, SHINGO.

114
00:09:18,666 --> 00:09:19,750
- YEAH.

115
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:21,625
- IF YOU DIDN'T 
KNOW IT ALREADY,

116
00:09:21,708 --> 00:09:23,541
THE NIGHT KIDS ARE 
A JOKE AROUND HERE.

117
00:09:23,625 --> 00:09:26,041
- WELL, THAT'S A HELL OF A NICE
WAY TO GREET AN OLD FRIEND.

118
00:09:26,125 --> 00:09:28,208
TAKESHI, I'D LIKE YOU
TO MEET SAYUKI.

119
00:09:28,291 --> 00:09:29,500
WE GREW UP TOGETHER.

120
00:09:31,791 --> 00:09:33,083
- HOW YOU DOING?

121
00:09:36,250 --> 00:09:38,166
- Takeshi:
DAMN, SHE'S HOT.

122
00:09:38,250 --> 00:09:40,416
- YOU MIGHT HAVE HEARD IT
ALREADY THROUGH THE GRAPEVINE,

123
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:42,166
BUT TAKESHI'S THE ONE
WHO RACED 'EM.

124
00:09:42,250 --> 00:09:43,666
- GLAD TO MEET YOU.

125
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:45,666
- CAN'T BELIEVE YOU
LOST TO THOSE DUDES

126
00:09:45,750 --> 00:09:48,625
ON YOUR HOME TURF. HOW COULD
YOU DO SOMETHING SO STUPID? 

127
00:09:48,708 --> 00:09:49,750
- ( exhales )

128
00:09:53,666 --> 00:09:55,500
Takeshi: I AM HERE
TO DEFEND GUNMA TONIGHT.

129
00:09:55,583 --> 00:09:57,666
AND BEFORE I'M DONE,
YOU'RE GONNA FIND YOURSELF

130
00:09:57,750 --> 00:09:59,458
BURIED DEEP AT THE BOTTOM
OF MYOGI VALLEY.

131
00:10:06,625 --> 00:10:08,458
- ( chuckles )

132
00:10:11,958 --> 00:10:13,291
- WHAT?

133
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:26,333
Takeshi: I CAN'T BELIEVE
THIS IS HAPPENING.

134
00:10:26,416 --> 00:10:27,875
BUT WE STILL GOT
A LONG WAY TO GO

135
00:10:27,958 --> 00:10:30,500
BEFORE THE FINISH LINE.

136
00:10:30,583 --> 00:10:32,666
IF I DON'T STOP THESE GUYS...

137
00:10:32,750 --> 00:10:35,333
THEN WHO THE HELL ELSE
IS GONNA BE ABLE TO?! 

138
00:10:46,333 --> 00:10:47,708
( gasps )

139
00:10:47,791 --> 00:10:48,666
( grunts )

140
00:10:51,333 --> 00:10:52,208
AAH!

141
00:11:04,291 --> 00:11:05,708
- ( gasping )

142
00:11:05,791 --> 00:11:07,666
- ( chuckles )

143
00:11:09,500 --> 00:11:11,416
- THEY'RE A TEAM OF
LAN-EVO RACERS.

144
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:13,458
CALL THEMSELVES
"THE EMPERORS."

145
00:11:13,541 --> 00:11:16,166
IT ALL WENT DOWN AFTER TAKESHI
HAD LOST TO THE RED SUNS

146
00:11:16,250 --> 00:11:18,000
IN AN UPHILL RACE.

147
00:11:18,083 --> 00:11:20,166
I DON'T THINK HE'D FULLY
GOTTEN OVER GETTING WHOOPED YET.

148
00:11:20,250 --> 00:11:21,666
HE MUST HAVE BEEN FEELING
PRETTY OUT OF SYNC

149
00:11:21,750 --> 00:11:24,750
TO FAIL TWICE LIKE THAT.
- WHATEVER.

150
00:11:24,833 --> 00:11:27,250
- HE'S NOT THE MOST CONSISTENT
PERSON ON THE PLANET,

151
00:11:27,333 --> 00:11:28,958
AND HE CERTAINLY
FOLDS UNDER PRESSURE.

152
00:11:29,041 --> 00:11:30,458
- TELL YOU WHAT, SHINGO,

153
00:11:30,541 --> 00:11:31,958
YOU DON'T YOU PUT
A FREAKING CORK IN IT?

154
00:11:32,041 --> 00:11:34,791
- BUT NOBODY CAN DRIVE
A THREE-TWO LIKE HE CAN.

155
00:11:34,875 --> 00:11:36,625
I GOTTA GIVE HIM THAT MUCH.

156
00:11:36,708 --> 00:11:38,791
IN FACT, I'D SAY HE'S PROBABLY
THE BEST THREE-TWO RACER

157
00:11:38,875 --> 00:11:40,791
WE GOT AROUND OUR REGION.

158
00:11:40,875 --> 00:11:42,625
BUT EVEN HE COULDN'T 
KEEP UP WITH THE FIRE

159
00:11:42,708 --> 00:11:44,625
BURNING OFF THE BACK
OF THAT LAN-EVO,

160
00:11:44,708 --> 00:11:46,250
WHICH LETS YOU KNOW
JUST HOW FAST THEY ARE.

161
00:11:46,333 --> 00:11:48,291
THEY SAID TO
GIVE THEM A MONTH

162
00:11:48,375 --> 00:11:50,791
AND THEY'D KNOCK OUT
ALL THE COMPETITION IN GUNMA.

163
00:11:50,875 --> 00:11:53,541
SOONER OR LATER 
THEY'LL BE HERE.

164
00:11:53,625 --> 00:11:55,375
SO YOU BETTER
WATCH YOUR BACK, SAYUKI.

165
00:11:55,458 --> 00:11:56,875
MYOGI'S CLOSE TO USUI.

166
00:11:56,958 --> 00:11:58,708
IT WON'T TAKE MUCH
FOR THEM TO GET TO YOU.

167
00:12:01,708 --> 00:12:04,250
- I KNOW.
THAT'S WHAT I'M LOOKING FOR.

168
00:12:04,333 --> 00:12:05,833
- ( gasps )

169
00:12:05,916 --> 00:12:08,208
- PEOPLE DON'T CALL US
IMPACT BLUE

170
00:12:08,291 --> 00:12:09,625
BECAUSE WE SIT ON OUR ASSES

171
00:12:09,708 --> 00:12:10,958
AND LET EVERY LOSER
WHO COMES THROUGH

172
00:12:11,041 --> 00:12:12,583
ROLL OVER US.

173
00:12:12,666 --> 00:12:14,583
- Takeshi:
MAN, THIS CHICK IS AGGRESSIVE.

174
00:12:14,666 --> 00:12:16,583
- I'M JUST TRYING TO HELP YOU.
GIVE YOU A LITTLE HEADS UP.

175
00:12:16,666 --> 00:12:18,250
YOU'RE BETTER OFF
AVOIDING THESE GUYS.

176
00:12:18,333 --> 00:12:21,625
YOU SHOULD KNOW BY NOW
TO TRUST WHAT I'M SAYING.

177
00:12:21,708 --> 00:12:24,250
- WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU
GETTING AT WITH THAT, SHINGO?

178
00:12:24,333 --> 00:12:26,333
YOU THINK WE'RE NOT GOOD
ENOUGH TO DEAL WITH THE JERKS,

179
00:12:26,416 --> 00:12:27,583
IS THAT IT?

180
00:12:27,666 --> 00:12:28,916
- I WOULDN'T SAY SOMETHING
LIKE THAT TO YOU.

181
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:30,916
YOU KNOW ME
BETTER THAN THAT.

182
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:32,083
- ( both gasp )

183
00:12:35,375 --> 00:12:36,708
- Takeshi: BOUNCY.

184
00:12:38,333 --> 00:12:39,750
- WE MIGHT JUST
BE CHICKS TO YOU,

185
00:12:39,833 --> 00:12:41,083
BUT DON'T COUNT US OUT.

186
00:12:41,166 --> 00:12:42,833
WE DON'T BACK DOWN
FROM ANYONE.

187
00:12:42,916 --> 00:12:44,291
NEVER HAVE, NEVER WILL.

188
00:12:44,375 --> 00:12:45,666
- ( stammers )

189
00:12:45,750 --> 00:12:48,000
- YEAH, I BELIEVE YOU.

190
00:12:48,083 --> 00:12:50,666
- IS THAT ALL
YOU HAVE TO SAY TO ME?

191
00:12:50,750 --> 00:12:52,375
GREAT, THEN I'M LEAVING.

192
00:12:55,541 --> 00:12:57,875
- SHE CAN BE SUCH
A STUBBORN PAIN IN THE ASS.

193
00:12:57,958 --> 00:13:00,250
DON'T YOU COME
CRYING TO ME, OKAY?

194
00:13:00,333 --> 00:13:02,083
SO IN CASE YOU HADN'T
FIGURED IT OUT,

195
00:13:02,166 --> 00:13:03,958
I BROUGHT YOU HERE
'CAUSE I WANTED HER TO KNOW

196
00:13:04,041 --> 00:13:06,458
JUST HOW DANGEROUS
THE EMPERORS ARE. 

197
00:13:06,541 --> 00:13:08,875
YOU COULD HAVE AT LEAST
TRIED TO HELP OUT.

198
00:13:08,958 --> 00:13:11,666
EARTH TO MORON,
ARE YOU EVEN LISTENING TO ME?

199
00:13:11,750 --> 00:13:13,708
- DUDE.

200
00:13:13,791 --> 00:13:15,833
SHE'S SO HOT.

201
00:13:17,791 --> 00:13:19,333
- HMM?

202
00:13:23,541 --> 00:13:25,666
- ALL RIGHT, BOYS,
DON'T ASK ME WHERE I HEARD IT,

203
00:13:25,750 --> 00:13:27,666
BUT I KNOW THAT
A LAN-EVO TEAM 

204
00:13:27,750 --> 00:13:30,416
CALLED THE EMPERORS ARE PLANNING
TO PULL AN ATTACK ON GUNMA.

205
00:13:30,500 --> 00:13:32,708
- A BUDDY OF MINE WAS TELLING
ME ABOUT THAT THE OTHER DAY.

206
00:13:32,791 --> 00:13:35,125
IT SEEMS EVERYONE'S BEEN
TALKING ABOUT THEM LATELY.

207
00:13:35,208 --> 00:13:37,125
- YEAH.  I HEARD SOME CRAP
ABOUT THEM CUTTING

208
00:13:37,208 --> 00:13:38,791
THE NIGHT KIDS 
STICKER IN HALF

209
00:13:38,875 --> 00:13:40,750
AND PUTTING IT UPSIDE DOWN
ON ONE OF THEIR SPOILERS. 

210
00:13:40,833 --> 00:13:42,666
SOME KIND OF
VICTORY THING THEY DO.

211
00:13:42,750 --> 00:13:44,333
- WHO WOULD PULL THAT?

212
00:13:44,416 --> 00:13:46,166
- YOU REALLY THINK THEY'RE
GONNA COME UP HERE?

213
00:13:46,250 --> 00:13:48,416
- WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO 
IF THEY SHOW UP, SAYUKI?

214
00:13:48,500 --> 00:13:50,208
YOU GONNA TAKE 'EM ON?

215
00:13:50,291 --> 00:13:52,833
- YOU KNOW, DUDE,
THAT'S A REALLY STUPID QUESTION.

216
00:13:52,916 --> 00:13:55,125
WOULDN'T YOU SAY SO, MAKO?

217
00:13:55,208 --> 00:13:57,333
- YEP.  ANY CHALLENGE
IS WORTH TAKING.

218
00:13:57,416 --> 00:13:59,083
WE'RE THE FASTEST 
USUI HAS TO OFFER.

219
00:13:59,166 --> 00:14:00,916
THEY DON'T CALL US 
IMPACT BLUE BECAUSE

220
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:02,250
WE DRAG AROUND THE CURVES.

221
00:14:04,416 --> 00:14:05,833
- SO THAT'S WHERE WE STAND.

222
00:14:05,916 --> 00:14:07,833
BUT WE NEED YOU GUYS 
TO HELP US OUT, OKAY?

223
00:14:07,916 --> 00:14:10,250
THE SECOND ANY ONE OF YOU
SEES THOSE LAN-EVOS,

224
00:14:10,333 --> 00:14:12,250
CALL ME ON MY CELL AND TELL
ME EXACTLY WHERE THEY ARE

225
00:14:12,333 --> 00:14:13,666
SO WE CAN TAKE THEM DOWN.

226
00:14:13,750 --> 00:14:16,208
- ( cheering )

227
00:14:29,875 --> 00:14:31,708
- IT'S BEEN TWO DAYS
AND WE HAVEN'T SEEN 

228
00:14:31,791 --> 00:14:33,916
OR HEARD A THING FROM
THE LAN-EVO GUYS.

229
00:14:38,041 --> 00:14:40,375
MAYBE THEY'RE NOT
COMING HERE TO USUI.

230
00:14:40,458 --> 00:14:42,375
I HAVE TO BE HONEST
WITH MYSELF.

231
00:14:42,458 --> 00:14:44,958
THERE'S A BIG PART OF ME
THAT'LL FEEL A HUGE RELIEF

232
00:14:45,041 --> 00:14:45,916
IF THEY DON'T.

233
00:14:48,875 --> 00:14:52,000
I KNOW I HAVEN'T BEEN
AT THE TOP OF MY GAME LATELY.

234
00:14:52,083 --> 00:14:54,791
AND IF I HAD TO SQUARE OFF
AGAINST THEM TONIGHT,

235
00:14:54,875 --> 00:14:56,958
I'M SURE IT WOULDN'T BE
THE BEST RACE I'VE EVER RUN.

236
00:14:57,041 --> 00:14:58,333
NOT BY A LONG SHOT.

237
00:15:08,083 --> 00:15:10,416
BUT I WANT TO CLEAR
THIS HAZE FROM MY MIND.

238
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:12,000
SOMEHOW.

239
00:15:12,083 --> 00:15:14,416
I JUST WANT TO FORGET
ABOUT IKETANI.

240
00:15:14,500 --> 00:15:16,916
I WANT THAT REJECTION
OUT OF MY MIND.

241
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:19,958
- COME ON!

242
00:15:20,041 --> 00:15:22,958
- ( Mako screams )

243
00:15:23,041 --> 00:15:24,458
SAYUKI, WHAT IS THIS?

244
00:15:24,541 --> 00:15:26,333
DO YOU WANT TO TELL ME
JUST WHAT IN THE HELL 

245
00:15:26,416 --> 00:15:27,958
YOU'RE DOING IN MY BATHROOM?

246
00:15:28,041 --> 00:15:29,666
- ARE YOU STUPID?
THIS ISN'T THE TIME

247
00:15:29,750 --> 00:15:31,958
FOR YOU TO BE LOUNGING
IN THE FREAKING BATH. 

248
00:15:32,041 --> 00:15:34,208
- WHAT'S GOING ON?

249
00:15:34,291 --> 00:15:36,250
- I CAME TO PICK YOU UP. 
WE'RE BLOWING THIS JOINT.

250
00:15:36,333 --> 00:15:37,708
NOW MOVE YOUR ASS.

251
00:15:37,791 --> 00:15:39,458
- I DON'T GET IT.
WHERE ARE WE GOING?

252
00:15:39,541 --> 00:15:41,083
- UP TO USUI PASS.

253
00:15:41,166 --> 00:15:43,666
THE LAN-EVO JERKS
JUST ROLLED INTO TOWN.

254
00:15:43,750 --> 00:15:44,958
- ( gasps )

255
00:15:47,250 --> 00:15:50,041
- HURRY AND PUT ON SOME 
UNDERWEAR FOR GOD SAKES.

256
00:15:50,125 --> 00:15:51,458
- JUST GIVE ME A SECOND,
YOU FREAK!

257
00:16:13,125 --> 00:16:14,958
- LAN-EVOS COMING UP
THE MOUNTAIN, GUYS. 

258
00:16:22,041 --> 00:16:23,958
- OH, MAN.
IT'S THE EMPERORS ALL RIGHT.

259
00:16:24,041 --> 00:16:25,541
I CAN'T BELIEVE
THEY ACTUALLY SHOWED UP.

260
00:16:25,625 --> 00:16:27,916
- WE NEED TO CALL
SAYUKI AND MAKO NOW.

261
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:28,875
- YEAH.

262
00:16:35,083 --> 00:16:37,958
- FOR REAL?
THE LAN-EVOS JUST SHOWED UP?

263
00:16:38,041 --> 00:16:41,500
- SAME DAMN EMPEROR JAG-OFFS
YOU TOLD ME ABOUT EARLIER.

264
00:16:41,583 --> 00:16:43,083
WE'RE ON OUR WAY
UP THERE RIGHT NOW,

265
00:16:43,166 --> 00:16:44,791
AND I THOUGHT
YOU'D WANT TO KNOW.

266
00:16:44,875 --> 00:16:47,083
- THANKS FOR THE HEADS UP.
- ( cellphone beeps )

267
00:16:47,166 --> 00:16:49,541
- HEY, TAKESHI.

268
00:16:49,625 --> 00:16:52,625
THE LAN-EVO SQUAD
JUST SHOWED UP IN USUI.

269
00:16:52,708 --> 00:16:55,125
- YOU SCREWING WITH ME?

270
00:16:55,208 --> 00:16:57,708
- I'M NOT.
NOW LET'S GO.

271
00:16:57,791 --> 00:16:59,250
- YOU GOT IT.

272
00:17:17,833 --> 00:17:20,125
- Rourke: ALL I SEE IS
A BUNCH OF DRIFT PUNKS

273
00:17:20,208 --> 00:17:22,458
WITH DUMBASS LOOKS
ON THEIR FACES.

274
00:17:22,541 --> 00:17:24,125
GUNMA DOESN'T SEEM LIKE
SUCH A KILLER PLACE

275
00:17:24,208 --> 00:17:26,375
FOR REAL RACERS.
THIS IS AMATEUR HOUR.

276
00:17:26,458 --> 00:17:28,208
- LET'S GET OUT OF HERE
AND TELL KYOICHI

277
00:17:28,291 --> 00:17:30,416
HE'S GOT AN EASY KILL WAITING.
- SURE.

278
00:17:33,083 --> 00:17:33,958
HUH?

279
00:18:05,333 --> 00:18:07,166
- HOW YOU FELLAS DOING?

280
00:18:07,250 --> 00:18:09,000
IF YOU CAME
LOOKING FOR A RACE,

281
00:18:09,083 --> 00:18:11,000
WE'LL TAKE THE CHALLENGE
'CAUSE OUR SIL-EIGHTY

282
00:18:11,083 --> 00:18:13,833
IS THE FASTEST CAR YOU'LL 
FIND ANYWHERE AROUND HERE.

283
00:18:13,916 --> 00:18:14,791
- ( gasps )

284
00:18:19,416 --> 00:18:21,500
- HEY, I GOT A QUESTION.
ANYTHING GOING ON

285
00:18:21,583 --> 00:18:23,166
BETWEEN YOU AND THAT
SIL-EIGHTY CHICK?

286
00:18:23,250 --> 00:18:24,916
I COULDN'T REALLY TELL
AT THE RESTAURANT.

287
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:27,583
- HMM.
ME AND SAYUKI, YOU SERIOUS?

288
00:18:27,666 --> 00:18:29,583
NAH, IT'S NOT LIKE THAT.
WE'RE JUST FRIENDS.

289
00:18:29,666 --> 00:18:32,041
THE TWO OF US HAVE BEEN FRIENDS
SINCE WE WERE KIDS.

290
00:18:32,125 --> 00:18:34,208
WE LIVED NEAR EACH OTHER,
WENT TO THE SAME SCHOOLS,

291
00:18:34,291 --> 00:18:37,250
THAT KIND OF STUFF, YOU KNOW.
WE'RE JUST REGULAR FRIENDS, MAN.

292
00:18:39,125 --> 00:18:41,208
- THAT'S COOL.
- I KNOW.

293
00:18:41,291 --> 00:18:43,625
OH, I JUST PUT IT TOGETHER.

294
00:18:43,708 --> 00:18:46,291
YOU TOTALLY DIG
AGGRESSIVE CHICKS, DON'T YOU?

295
00:18:46,375 --> 00:18:49,333
- UH-- WELL...

296
00:18:49,416 --> 00:18:52,125
- FORGET HER. SHE'S A
STRONG-WILLED PAIN IN THE ASS

297
00:18:52,208 --> 00:18:54,166
WHO'LL WALK ALL OVER YOU.

298
00:18:54,250 --> 00:18:57,625
YEAH, SHE DOESN'T LISTEN TO
ANYTHING ANYONE ELSE HAS TO SAY.

299
00:18:57,708 --> 00:18:58,958
DOES HER OWN THING.

300
00:18:59,041 --> 00:19:00,625
EVEN IF THEY ARE
THE FASTEST IN USUI,

301
00:19:00,708 --> 00:19:02,625
THEY DON'T STAND A CHANCE
AGAINST THE LAN-EVOS.

302
00:19:02,708 --> 00:19:06,208
SHE THINKS THEY'RE GONNA BE
EASY TO WHIP, BUT SHE'S WRONG.

303
00:19:06,291 --> 00:19:08,208
EVEN I CAN ADMIT
THEIR DRIFT TECHNIQUE

304
00:19:08,291 --> 00:19:10,458
IS AN AMAZING THING,
FOR FREAKING REAL.

305
00:19:10,541 --> 00:19:11,875
THERE'S PROBABLY
NO ONE IN USUI

306
00:19:11,958 --> 00:19:13,708
WHO COULD HOLD A CANDLE
TO THOSE CHICKS.

307
00:19:13,791 --> 00:19:17,083
BUT WITH PURE SPEED RACING,
THEY GOT NO EXPERIENCE.

308
00:19:17,166 --> 00:19:18,833
THAT KIND OF DRIVING
REQUIRES CONTROL

309
00:19:18,916 --> 00:19:20,583
THAT'S SIMPLY
OUT OF THEIR REACH.

310
00:19:20,666 --> 00:19:22,666
THEIR CONTROL'S GOOD, YEAH.

311
00:19:22,750 --> 00:19:25,416
BUT IT'S NOT-- I DON'T KNOW.
IT'S JUST NOT CRISP ENOUGH. 

312
00:19:25,500 --> 00:19:28,375
THEY'LL BE OUTCLASSED
BY A SERIOUS FOUR-WHEEL DRIVE.

313
00:19:30,958 --> 00:19:33,250
YOU KNOW EXACTLY WHAT
I'M TALKING ABOUT.

314
00:19:33,333 --> 00:19:34,291
YOU'VE BEEN THERE.

315
00:19:37,458 --> 00:19:39,666
AND I'M NOT SAYING THEY'RE 
SLOW BECAUSE THEY'RE CHICKS

316
00:19:39,750 --> 00:19:41,833
OR ANYTHING
TOTALLY STUPID LIKE THAT.

317
00:19:41,916 --> 00:19:43,666
I JUST KNOW THE FACTS
AS THEY STAND.

318
00:19:48,750 --> 00:19:51,666
- OH, SO YOU'RE IN
A SIL-EIGHTY, HUH?

319
00:19:51,750 --> 00:19:54,041
AND YOU'RE CHICKS TO BOOT.
THAT'S FUN.

320
00:19:56,416 --> 00:19:58,208
LOOKS LIKE A GOOD TIME.
WHAT DO YOU SAY WE PLAY

321
00:19:58,291 --> 00:19:59,666
A LITTLE ROUND-AND-ROUND?

322
00:19:59,750 --> 00:20:01,125
- I DON'T THINK THAT'S
SUCH A GOOD IDEA.

323
00:20:01,208 --> 00:20:02,791
KYOICHI WILL KICK YOUR ASS.

324
00:20:02,875 --> 00:20:04,208
YOU KNOW THAT'S NOT 
WHY WE'RE HERE, MAN.

325
00:20:04,291 --> 00:20:05,791
WE CAME UP HERE
TO SCOUT THE PLACE,

326
00:20:05,875 --> 00:20:07,458
AND THAT'S ALL
WE'RE SUPPOSED TO DO.

327
00:20:07,541 --> 00:20:10,041
- SHUT UP.  DON'T BE SUCH
A BUZZ-KILL, NANCY.

328
00:20:10,125 --> 00:20:12,208
I MEAN WE CAME ALL THE WAY
UP HERE, DIDN'T WE?

329
00:20:12,291 --> 00:20:13,500
SO BACK OFF.

330
00:20:13,583 --> 00:20:15,000
I DON'T SEE THE DAMAGE IN US

331
00:20:15,083 --> 00:20:16,708
HAVING A LITTLE FUN
WHILE WE'RE AT IT. 

332
00:20:16,791 --> 00:20:19,500
AS LONG AS I WIN.

333
00:20:19,583 --> 00:20:21,125
- SURE, DUDE.
BUT WHAT IF THEY'RE GOOD

334
00:20:21,208 --> 00:20:22,416
AND YOU ACTUALLY
LOSE TO THEM?

335
00:20:22,500 --> 00:20:24,958
- DON'T INSULT ME.

336
00:20:25,041 --> 00:20:27,291
WHY DON'T YOU GO AHEAD AND
EXPLAIN SOMETHING TO ME, REN.

337
00:20:27,375 --> 00:20:29,875
HOW COULD MY BADASS EVO FOUR
LOSE TO A COUPLE OF

338
00:20:29,958 --> 00:20:33,000
HAIRSPRAY SNORTING BIMBOS
LIKE THOSE TWO CHICKS?

339
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:37,166
- HEAR THAT, MAKO?
HE SCREWED UP NOW.

340
00:20:37,250 --> 00:20:39,583
THAT'LL BE THE LAST
DUMB THING HE SAYS TODAY.

341
00:20:39,666 --> 00:20:41,416
- PEOPLE WHO
INSULT WOMEN RACERS

342
00:20:41,500 --> 00:20:44,000
JUST BECAUSE THEY'RE WOMEN
ARE THE WORST KIND OF JERKS.

343
00:20:44,083 --> 00:20:46,958
SO THAT'S THE LAST STRAW.
WE'RE NOT GOING EASY ON YOU.

344
00:20:47,041 --> 00:20:48,916
- ( engine starts, revs )

345
00:20:51,833 --> 00:20:54,333
- Sayuki: HER EYES GOT
THAT SERIOUS LOOK IN THEM.

346
00:20:54,416 --> 00:20:57,333
SHE'S FASTER THAN A HYDROPLANER
WHEN SHE LOOKS LIKE THAT.

347
00:20:57,416 --> 00:20:59,708
'CAUSE THAT'S WHEN
HER EMOTIONS FUEL HER.

348
00:21:09,416 --> 00:21:11,750
WE'RE GONNA RUN 
A DOWNHILL RACE.

349
00:21:11,833 --> 00:21:13,333
AND SINCE USUI'S
A NARROW COURSE,

350
00:21:13,416 --> 00:21:14,750
WE'RE GONNA DO IT
CAT-AND-MOUSE STYLE.

351
00:21:14,833 --> 00:21:17,166
I'M SURE YOU'RE
FAMILIAR WITH IT.

352
00:21:17,250 --> 00:21:19,375
IF THE MOUSE GETS AWAY,
IT'S OVER.

353
00:21:19,458 --> 00:21:21,875
IF NOT, WE KEEP SWITCHING
UNTIL SOMEONE WINS.

354
00:21:21,958 --> 00:21:23,791
YOU COOL WITH THAT?

355
00:21:23,875 --> 00:21:25,875
- THAT'LL WORK.

356
00:21:25,958 --> 00:21:28,125
- JUST TELL ME WHICH
POSITION YOU WANT FIRST.

357
00:21:28,208 --> 00:21:30,583
SINCE YOU'RE THE OUTSIDER,
I'M GONNA GIVE YOU THE CHOICE.

358
00:21:30,666 --> 00:21:33,625
- YOU KNOW, I'LL FOLLOW YOU
ON THE FIRST RUN.

359
00:21:33,708 --> 00:21:36,625
THAT WAY I CAN CHECK OUT WHAT
YOU'RE MADE OF FROM BEHIND.

360
00:21:36,708 --> 00:21:38,791
- SOUNDS LIKE WE'RE
READY TO GET STARTED THEN.

361
00:21:38,875 --> 00:21:40,208
AFTER WE EXIT THE FIRST TURN,

362
00:21:40,291 --> 00:21:41,625
WE'LL KICK IT UP
TO FULL SPEED.

363
00:21:41,708 --> 00:21:43,291
THAT'LL BE THE START
OF THE RACE.

364
00:21:43,375 --> 00:21:45,208
THINK YOU'RE CAPABLE
OF REMEMBERING ALL OF THAT?

365
00:21:45,291 --> 00:21:46,791
OR IS THAT TOO MUCH?

366
00:21:46,875 --> 00:21:50,791
- I'M GOOD.  LET'S DO IT.

367
00:21:52,291 --> 00:21:54,291
- HEY, YOU GONNA BE OKAY
DOING THIS ALONE?

368
00:21:54,375 --> 00:21:56,375
- DIDN'T I JUST SAY
A SECOND AGO THAT I WAS GOOD?

369
00:21:56,458 --> 00:21:58,291
I'M ONE OF THE TOP 
RACERS ON OUR TEAM.

370
00:21:58,375 --> 00:22:00,750
HE'LL, PAL, I'M EVEN
BETTER THAN YOU.

371
00:22:00,833 --> 00:22:02,833
I'M MORE THAN POSITIVE
THAT MY EVO FOUR

372
00:22:02,916 --> 00:22:05,666
IS GONNA WIPE THE ROAD
WITH SOME LAME-ASS SIL-EIGHTY

373
00:22:05,750 --> 00:22:07,541
DRIVEN BY TWO CHICKS.

374
00:22:07,625 --> 00:22:09,333
- ( engines revving )

375
00:22:14,916 --> 00:22:16,875
- RIGHT.  LET'S GO.

376
00:22:16,958 --> 00:22:18,708
- WE'VE GOT THIS IN THE BAG.

377
00:22:18,791 --> 00:22:21,875
I'M NOT LOSING TO SOME GUY 
WHO INSULTS FEMALE DRIVERS.

378
00:22:21,958 --> 00:22:24,291
- YOU LOOK READY. YOU REALLY
THINK YOU'RE UP FOR THIS?

379
00:22:24,375 --> 00:22:26,666
- WHENEVER YOU ARE, SAYUKI.

380
00:22:28,208 --> 00:22:29,166
- HIT THE GAS.

381
00:22:54,500 --> 00:22:56,875
- HUH.  SHOULD BE AN EASY WIN.

382
00:22:56,958 --> 00:22:58,791
EVEN ON ITS WORST DAY,
HIS EVO FOUR

383
00:22:58,875 --> 00:23:01,208
WOULD NEVER LOSE TO SOME
SPENT SIL-EIGHTY.

384
00:23:01,291 --> 00:23:03,791
- I'M SURPRISED THEY'RE
REALLY GOING THROUGH WITH THIS.

385
00:23:03,875 --> 00:23:06,041
WHEN IT COMES DOWN TO IT,
WOMEN CAN HAVE A HELL OF A LOT

386
00:23:06,125 --> 00:23:07,458
MORE COURAGE THAN MEN DO.

387
00:23:07,541 --> 00:23:09,041
- BUT CAN THEY
BEAT THE EMPERORS?

388
00:23:09,125 --> 00:23:10,791
I MEAN, THOSE GUYS LAID WASTE
TO THE NIGHT KIDS

389
00:23:10,875 --> 00:23:12,291
NOT TOO LONG AGO.

390
00:23:12,375 --> 00:23:14,791
- THAT EVO FOUR IS AN 
EXTREMELY HIGH-POWERED

391
00:23:14,875 --> 00:23:16,333
FOUR-WHEEL DRIVE.

392
00:23:16,416 --> 00:23:17,875
ANYONE ELSE
WOULD HAVE RUN AWAY.

393
00:23:17,958 --> 00:23:20,041
BUT IF SAYUKI AND MAKO
CAN'T WIN,

394
00:23:20,125 --> 00:23:21,875
THEN I CAN'T THINK OF ANYBODY
WHO'S GOT THE SKILLS

395
00:23:21,958 --> 00:23:23,750
OR THE CAR TO DO IT.
- RIGHT.

396
00:23:23,833 --> 00:23:25,833
AND I DON'T KNOW WHO IT WAS 
THAT NAMED THEM IMPACT BLUE,

397
00:23:25,916 --> 00:23:27,333
BUT THEY CERTAINLY
DESERVED IT.

398
00:23:27,416 --> 00:23:28,791
THEY'RE USUI'S FASTEST
BY A MILE.

399
00:23:28,875 --> 00:23:30,833
- ALL WE CAN DO NOW
IS BELIEVE IN THEM.

400
00:23:30,916 --> 00:23:32,500
BECAUSE IT SEEMS LIKE
WE BOTH HAVE FAITH

401
00:23:32,583 --> 00:23:34,083
IN ONE CENTRAL THING:

402
00:23:34,166 --> 00:23:36,458
THAT THE SIL-EIGHTY
IS THE BEST HERE.

403
00:23:48,541 --> 00:23:50,500
- NOT BAD FOR A COUPLE
OF DUMB CHICKS,

404
00:23:50,583 --> 00:23:52,416
BUT IT'S THEIR COURSE
SO THEY KNOW BETTER THAN ANYONE

405
00:23:52,500 --> 00:23:53,375
HOW TO ATTACK IT.

406
00:23:56,416 --> 00:23:58,500
- NO CARS AHEAD OF US, GIRL.
YOU CAN KICK IT OUT

407
00:23:58,583 --> 00:24:00,500
AND DRIFT RIGHT ON
THROUGH THIS CORNER.

408
00:24:06,208 --> 00:24:08,375
- ( chuckles )
MY EVO FOUR'S DRIFT

409
00:24:08,458 --> 00:24:10,500
IS MORE POWERFUL THAN ANY
PIECE OF CRAP FR'S DRIFT

410
00:24:10,583 --> 00:24:11,958
BY A LONG SHOT.

411
00:24:12,041 --> 00:24:14,541
WHAT I GOT IS A HIGH-SPEED
FOUR-WHEEL DRIVE DRIFT

412
00:24:14,625 --> 00:24:16,958
WITH AN ENGINE
ALWAYS ON FULL BLAST.

413
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:21,875
- ( tires screech )

414
00:24:28,750 --> 00:24:31,208
- ( gasps ) MAKO,
YOU'RE DOING GREAT, SISTER.

415
00:24:31,291 --> 00:24:33,541
GRIP THE NEXT CORNER
AND HUG THE INNER WALL.

416
00:24:33,625 --> 00:24:35,125
YOU'LL SKIP LIKE A STONE.

417
00:24:42,291 --> 00:24:45,166
SO FAR WE'RE ABOUT EVEN.

418
00:24:45,250 --> 00:24:48,000
I'M NOT SURE IF IT'S
THE EVO FOUR ITSELF,

419
00:24:48,083 --> 00:24:52,166
OR THE DRIVER'S TECHNIQUE THAT'S
LETTING HIM KEEP UP WITH US.

420
00:24:57,291 --> 00:24:58,833
- IT'S LIKE YOU WERE
SAYING EARLIER,

421
00:24:58,916 --> 00:25:00,833
THE SWINGING DRIFT INVOLVES
SO MANY VARIABLES

422
00:25:00,916 --> 00:25:02,666
YOU KIND OF HAVE TO BE 
A MASTER OF ALL TRADES.

423
00:25:02,750 --> 00:25:05,291
EVERYTHING DEPENDS ON 
HOW YOU USE THE TIRES.

424
00:25:05,375 --> 00:25:07,125
- YEAH.

425
00:25:07,208 --> 00:25:10,000
- SO WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
YOU SAW THIS SIL-EIGHTY RACE?

426
00:25:10,083 --> 00:25:11,583
HAS IT BEEN LIKE
YEARS OR WHAT?

427
00:25:11,666 --> 00:25:13,416
- NO, IT'S BEEN
SINCE LAST SPRING.

428
00:25:13,500 --> 00:25:16,250
- THEN MAYBE HER DRIVING STYLE'S
CHANGED A LITTLE BIT.

429
00:25:16,333 --> 00:25:17,666
- HUH?

430
00:25:17,750 --> 00:25:19,833
- I'VE EXPERIENCED IT TOO,
YOU KNOW.

431
00:25:19,916 --> 00:25:22,250
AFTER A HORRIFYING LOSS,
EVEN THE BEST RACER

432
00:25:22,333 --> 00:25:24,000
CAN REALLY CHANGE HIS TONE.

433
00:25:24,083 --> 00:25:26,625
SOMETIMES FOR THE BETTER,
AND SOMETIMES FOR THE WORSE.

434
00:25:26,708 --> 00:25:28,708
- YEAH.

435
00:25:28,791 --> 00:25:31,041
- THERE ARE PLENTY OF
TALENTED RACERS IN THE WORLD.

436
00:25:31,125 --> 00:25:35,041
LIKE AKINA'S EIGHT-SIX.
HE KNOWS WHAT HE'S DOING.

437
00:25:35,125 --> 00:25:36,875
THAT'S AN FR RACER WHO
COULD BEAT THE PANTS

438
00:25:36,958 --> 00:25:38,250
OFF A FOUR-WHEEL DRIVE.

439
00:25:38,333 --> 00:25:40,583
- BUT THAT EIGHT-SIX
IS AN EXCEPTION NOT THE RULE,

440
00:25:40,666 --> 00:25:42,083
YOU KNOW THAT.

441
00:25:42,166 --> 00:25:43,416
IT PROBABLY WOULD HAVE
BEEN A DIFFERENT STORY

442
00:25:43,500 --> 00:25:45,125
IF THOSE GIRLS HAD
EVEN HAD A CHANCE 

443
00:25:45,208 --> 00:25:47,208
