00:31:01,291 --> 00:31:02,791
- THAT'S A LOAD OF CRAP.

519
00:31:02,875 --> 00:31:05,166
HE ACTUALLY HAD A PRETTY
TIGHT GRIP ON HIS STYLE.

520
00:31:05,250 --> 00:31:07,958
IF WE RACED HIM BEFORE
HE RACED AKINA'S EIGHT-SIX,

521
00:31:08,041 --> 00:31:09,375
IT MIGHT HAVE BEEN
A CHALLENGE FOR YOU,

522
00:31:09,458 --> 00:31:11,125
BUT IT TIMED OUT JUST RIGHT.

523
00:31:11,208 --> 00:31:13,375
LESS ANGLED CORNERING
HAS BEEN OUR FOCUS

524
00:31:13,458 --> 00:31:15,625
EVER SINCE OUR LOSS. 
WE'RE GETTING BETTER.

525
00:31:15,708 --> 00:31:18,083
AND YOU'VE PROVED THAT 
WITH EVERY SINGLE TURN.

526
00:31:23,791 --> 00:31:27,375
BUT AT C-121 WHEN WE 
WENT IN FOR THE KILL,

527
00:31:27,458 --> 00:31:29,541
YOU SLIPPED RIGHT BACK
INTO YOUR FLASHY,

528
00:31:29,625 --> 00:31:31,666
DRAMATIC STYLE OF DRIFTING.

529
00:31:31,750 --> 00:31:35,375
- I GUESS I ENTERED THAT CORNER 
A LOT FASTER THAN I SHOULD HAVE.

530
00:31:35,458 --> 00:31:37,375
IT'S SAD. I'M ALMOST
GETTING NERVOUS

531
00:31:37,458 --> 00:31:39,833
JUST THINKING ABOUT IT NOW.
( chuckles )

532
00:31:39,916 --> 00:31:42,375
- WELL, IT SURE AS HELL WASN'T
FUNNY LAST NIGHT, OKAY?

533
00:31:42,458 --> 00:31:44,833
I THOUGHT I WAS GONNA
FREAKING DIE.

534
00:31:44,916 --> 00:31:48,000
I GOTTA SAY, YOU'RE ONE HECK
OF AN EMOTIONAL RACER, MAKO.

535
00:31:48,083 --> 00:31:50,166
YOU CHANGE INTO SOMEONE ELSE
WHEN YOU GET BEHIND

536
00:31:50,250 --> 00:31:51,833
THE WHEEL OF THAT CAR.

537
00:31:54,083 --> 00:31:57,875
- I FEEL THIS HUGE
SENSE OF RELIEF RIGHT NOW.

538
00:32:02,041 --> 00:32:04,416
BUT I STILL HAVE 
A LONG WAY TO GO.

539
00:32:04,500 --> 00:32:07,000
LIKE I'M CHASING AFTER
SOMETHING THAT'S JUST 

540
00:32:07,083 --> 00:32:09,000
WAY BEYOND THAT BLUE SKY,
YOU KNOW?

541
00:32:09,083 --> 00:32:10,375
SOMETHING INTANGIBLE.

542
00:32:13,041 --> 00:32:15,916
I'M NOT GONNA NEED
A MAN FOR A LONG TIME.

543
00:32:17,083 --> 00:32:20,833
JUST YOU WATCH ME, IKETANI.

544
00:32:20,916 --> 00:32:22,125
BANG.

545
00:32:22,208 --> 00:32:24,708
- ( Iketani sneezes )

546
00:32:24,791 --> 00:32:26,208
- YOU CATCH A COLD
OR SOMETHING?

547
00:32:26,291 --> 00:32:28,458
'CAUSE YOU SOUND LIKE
ABSOLUTE HELL.

548
00:32:28,541 --> 00:32:30,416
- NO, I DON'T THINK SO.
I'M COOL.

549
00:32:47,250 --> 00:32:49,791
- YOU'RE KIND OF WOBBLING
AS WE GO AROUND THE CURVES.

550
00:32:49,875 --> 00:32:51,291
- I CAN'T HELP IT.  DAMN.

551
00:32:51,375 --> 00:32:53,041
YESTERDAY'S SNOW 
HAS FROZEN SOLID,

552
00:32:53,125 --> 00:32:54,666
AND IT'S MAKING ME
SLIDE ALL OVER THE ROAD.

553
00:32:54,750 --> 00:32:56,541
GUESS MY STUDLESS TIRES
AREN'T REALLY

554
00:32:56,625 --> 00:32:58,583
CUTTING THE MUSTARD
OUT HERE.

555
00:33:00,750 --> 00:33:01,625
( gasps )

556
00:33:05,750 --> 00:33:06,666
OH!

557
00:33:09,666 --> 00:33:11,750
WHAT?
HOW'S THAT CAR DOING IT?

558
00:33:11,833 --> 00:33:14,583
IT'S GOT STUDLESS TIRES TOO.

559
00:33:17,166 --> 00:33:18,458
UNBELIEVABLE.

560
00:33:23,166 --> 00:33:24,916
- Sayuki:
WHOA!  WATCH OUT!

561
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:27,708
WHOA!
LOOK OUT, LOOK OUT!

562
00:33:27,791 --> 00:33:29,708
AAH!

563
00:33:29,791 --> 00:33:33,208
( screaming )

564
00:33:33,291 --> 00:33:36,083
NOT AGAIN.
GO RIGHT, RIGHT!

565
00:33:36,166 --> 00:33:38,208
NO!  NO!  CRAP.

566
00:33:38,291 --> 00:33:39,666
OH, DAMN IT.

567
00:33:39,750 --> 00:33:41,416
OH, WHY?

568
00:33:41,500 --> 00:33:42,791
- SAYUKI, YOU COOL?

569
00:33:42,875 --> 00:33:44,166
- THAT SUCKED!

570
00:33:44,250 --> 00:33:46,750
THE SNOW'S FROZEN SOLID
LIKE A ROCK.

571
00:33:46,833 --> 00:33:48,166
- SO YOU OKAY OR WHAT?

572
00:33:54,041 --> 00:33:55,500
- HMM.

573
00:34:09,208 --> 00:34:11,083
THIS IS FLIPPING ANNOYING.

574
00:34:11,166 --> 00:34:13,958
WE STARTED SNOWBOARDING
AT THE SAME TIME,

575
00:34:14,041 --> 00:34:15,291
AND HERE YOU ARE
MAKING IT LOOK LIKE

576
00:34:15,375 --> 00:34:17,041
THE EASIEST THING
IN THE WORLD.

577
00:34:17,125 --> 00:34:18,166
- ( chuckles )

578
00:34:18,250 --> 00:34:19,875
- LOOK, I HATE TO ADMIT IT,

579
00:34:19,958 --> 00:34:21,958
BUT OTHER CHICKS DON'T HAVE
YOUR ATHLETIC TALENT.

580
00:34:22,041 --> 00:34:23,708
