GOT IT?

637
00:36:24,583 --> 00:36:26,250
- I'LL KEEP
MY MOUTH SHUT.

638
00:36:26,333 --> 00:36:28,083
WHAT ABOUT YOU, SAYUKI?

639
00:36:28,166 --> 00:36:29,958
YOU GOT A SPECIAL GUY
ON THE SIDE THESE DAYS?

640
00:36:30,041 --> 00:36:32,000
- ARE YOU KIDDING?

641
00:36:32,083 --> 00:36:33,833
- TAKESHI WAS
TALKING ABOUT YOU.

642
00:36:33,916 --> 00:36:35,291
THE GUY'S DEVELOPED A CRUSH.

643
00:36:35,375 --> 00:36:37,500
YOU INTERESTED IN SOME
NIGHT KID ACTION?

644
00:36:39,041 --> 00:36:40,000
- UH...

645
00:36:59,166 --> 00:37:00,458
- YOU'RE PRETTY GOOD.

646
00:37:00,541 --> 00:37:02,125
SO HOW LONG HAVE YOU
BEEN SNOWBOARDING?

647
00:37:02,208 --> 00:37:03,458
- I JUST STARTED LAST YEAR.

648
00:37:03,541 --> 00:37:05,125
- THAT'S REALLY AMAZING.

649
00:37:05,208 --> 00:37:07,291
I DON'T KNOW MANY GIRLS
WHO CAN GO AS FAST AS YOU.

650
00:37:07,375 --> 00:37:09,583
I MEAN, THIS KIND OF SNOW
IS MORE FOR THE SEASONED.

651
00:37:09,666 --> 00:37:12,125
- WHAT CAN I SAY?
IT'S EXCITING FOR ME.

652
00:37:12,208 --> 00:37:13,541
MORE SO THAN A LOT OF
OTHER STUFF.

653
00:37:13,625 --> 00:37:15,291
WHEN I REALLY GET
INTO SOMETHING,

654
00:37:15,375 --> 00:37:18,208
I TOTALLY FOCUS ON THAT THING
SO IT'S ALL I CAN SEE.

655
00:37:18,291 --> 00:37:21,125
- HMM.

656
00:37:31,833 --> 00:37:33,166
- SO TELL ME, MAKO,

657
00:37:33,250 --> 00:37:34,416
YOU BEEN HAVING
ANY THOUGHTS ABOUT

658
00:37:34,500 --> 00:37:36,041
SHINGO'S FOUR-EYED BUDDY?

659
00:37:36,125 --> 00:37:38,583
- NO, NOT UNTIL
YOU BROUGHT HIM UP.

660
00:37:38,666 --> 00:37:40,750
HE'S NICE.
JUST SEEMS KIND OF SERIOUS.

661
00:37:40,833 --> 00:37:42,958
I GUESS THAT'S NOT 
A BAD THING THOUGH.

662
00:37:43,041 --> 00:37:44,250
- IS THAT ALL?

663
00:37:44,333 --> 00:37:46,166
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN
"IS THAT ALL?"

664
00:37:46,250 --> 00:37:49,708
I JUST MET THE GUY. I DON'T
HAVE MUCH OF AN OPINION YET.

665
00:37:49,791 --> 00:37:51,833
- Sayuki:
YEAH RIGHT.  I CAN TELL.

666
00:37:51,916 --> 00:37:52,875
THEY'VE GOT SOME CHEMISTRY

667
00:37:52,958 --> 00:37:54,750
BUBBLING BETWEEN
THE TWO OF THEM.

668
00:37:54,833 --> 00:37:57,416
OH, I FORGOT TO TELL YOU,
I HEARD SOMETHING INTERESTING

669
00:37:57,500 --> 00:37:58,666
THE OTHER DAY.

670
00:37:58,750 --> 00:38:00,625
RYOSUKE TAKAHASHI
OF THE RED SUNS

671
00:38:00,708 --> 00:38:02,291
IS RECRUITING RACERS.

672
00:38:02,375 --> 00:38:03,708
HE'S GATHERING TOGETHER
A NEW TEAM,

673
00:38:03,791 --> 00:38:05,208
AND I HEAR THAT HE MAY
EVEN BE PUTTING

674
00:38:05,291 --> 00:38:07,208
AKINA'S EIGHT-SIX ON IT.

675
00:38:07,291 --> 00:38:09,291
IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE SOME KIND
OF SPECIAL TRAVELING TEAM

676
00:38:09,375 --> 00:38:11,166
RUNNING AROUND
TO OTHER REGIONS.

677
00:38:11,250 --> 00:38:15,333
- YOU'RE MESSING WITH ME.
THAT'S NOT TRUE.

678
00:38:15,416 --> 00:38:16,875
OF COURSE IT IS.

679
00:38:16,958 --> 00:38:18,958
AND I REALLY ADMIRE
THE CONCEPT.

680
00:38:19,041 --> 00:38:20,958
THE WHOLE IDEA OF
NEVER STAYING IN ONE PLACE

681
00:38:21,041 --> 00:38:22,625
KEEPS THEM ALWAYS
MOVING FORWARD.

682
00:38:22,708 --> 00:38:24,291
IT'S REALLY PROGRESSIVE
FOR DRIVERS.

683
00:38:24,375 --> 00:38:25,958
- HMM.

684
00:38:26,041 --> 00:38:27,625
- THEY'RE SO BADASS,
IT ALMOST MAKES ME

685
00:38:27,708 --> 00:38:29,208
HATE THEM A LITTLE BIT.

686
00:38:29,291 --> 00:38:32,250
THEY'VE GOT SOME
SERIOUS CHARISMA GOING ON.

687
00:38:32,333 --> 00:38:33,791
( sighs )

688
00:38:33,875 --> 00:38:36,208
I WISH I COULD SEE
TAKUMI AGAIN.

689
00:38:36,291 --> 00:38:39,208
I WONDER IF HE'S BEEN DOING
WELL THESE PAST FEW WEEKS.

690
00:38:39,291 --> 00:38:42,291
I BET YOU ANYTHING
HE'S LOOKING AS HOT AS EVER.

691
00:38:42,375 --> 00:38:45,250
( chuckles ) THAT'S SOMETHING
I'M NEVER WRONG ABOUT.

692
00:38:45,333 --> 00:38:48,541
- YEAH. YOU DO HAVE
GOOD TASTE IN MEN. 

693
00:38:48,625 --> 00:38:50,250
- OH, GIRL.

694
00:38:50,333 --> 00:38:52,833
I'M REALLY HOPING TO GET
MY RACE ON SOON.

695
00:38:52,916 --> 00:38:54,416
YOU KNOW THE ROAD
ON THE WAY HERE

696
00:38:54,500 --> 00:38:55,458
ACTUALLY LOOKED
KIND OF NICE.

697
00:38:55,541 --> 00:38:56,833
I THINK IT WOULD BE
A TOTAL BLAST

698
00:38:56,916 --> 00:38:58,416
TO GIVE IT A RUN SOMETIME.

699
00:38:58,500 --> 00:39:01,541
I DIDN'T SEE ANY SNOW
DOWN TOWARD THE BOTTOM.

700
00:39:01,625 --> 00:39:04,500
- ( chuckles ) YOU KNOW, I WAS
THINKING THE EXACT SAME THING.

701
00:39:04,583 --> 00:39:06,500
YOU WANT TO GO CHECK IT OUT
WHEN WE'RE FINISHED?

702
00:39:06,583 --> 00:39:08,416
- THAT SOUNDS KILLER.

703
00:39:08,500 --> 00:39:10,333
WE'RE JUST SUCKERS
FOR RACING.

704
00:39:15,916 --> 00:39:17,750
- Keisuke: I'M SO BORED.

705
00:39:17,833 --> 00:39:21,291
THE PASS IS
TOO SNOWY TO RACE.

706
00:39:21,375 --> 00:39:23,375
- YOU KNOW KEISUKE,
THOSE WHO CAN CONQUER

707
00:39:23,458 --> 00:39:25,208
THE PASS IN WINTER CAN DO IT
EASIER IN THE SUMMER.

708
00:39:25,291 --> 00:39:26,875
- HUH?

709
00:39:26,958 --> 00:39:28,875
- OUR PROJECT ISN'T
GONNA GET GEARED UP GO

710
00:39:28,958 --> 00:39:30,875
UNTIL THIS SPRING
AT ITS EARLIEST. 

711
00:39:30,958 --> 00:39:33,208
WE'RE CERTAINLY NOT GONNA MAKE
ANY PROGRESS WHEN WE DO START 

712
00:39:33,291 --> 00:39:36,291
IF WE SIT ON OUR HANDS
ALL WINTER LONG COMPLAINING.

713
00:39:36,375 --> 00:39:38,500
GET OUT ON THAT SNOWY ROAD
AND START DRIVING.

714
00:39:38,583 --> 00:39:40,291
- WHAT?

715
00:39:40,375 --> 00:39:42,041
- CLEAR YOUR MIND
OF EVERYTHING,

716
00:39:42,125 --> 00:39:43,625
AND GET YOUR ASS
ON THAT FROZEN ROAD

717
00:39:43,708 --> 00:39:45,958
DAY AND NIGHT
AND EVERY SECOND IN BETWEEN.

718
00:39:49,041 --> 00:39:50,458
YOU'LL SEE THE EFFECTS
OF YOUR HARD WORK

719
00:39:50,541 --> 00:39:52,041
IN THE SPRING WHEN
THE SNOW THAWS

720
00:39:52,125 --> 00:39:53,791
AND YOU CHANGE BACK
TO HIGH-GRIP TIRES.

721
00:39:53,875 --> 00:39:55,458
IT'LL BE A MASSIVE DIFFERENCE.

722
00:39:55,541 --> 00:39:57,625
YOUR SENSES WILL BE SHARPER
THAN THEY'VE EVER BEEN,

723
00:39:57,708 --> 00:39:59,875
AND YOUR DRIVING SKILLS
WILL BE DRAMATICALLY REFINED.

724
00:39:59,958 --> 00:40:01,708
YOU'LL BE LIKE
A WHOLE NEW MAN.

725
00:40:01,791 --> 00:40:04,083
LISTEN, KEISUKE.

726
00:40:04,166 --> 00:40:06,750
WE'RE GONNA CREATE A NEW
UNBEATABLE RECORD AT EVERY PASS.

727
00:40:06,833 --> 00:40:08,500
THAT'S HOW WE BUILD
OURSELVES AS LEGENDS.

728
00:40:08,583 --> 00:40:10,500
ARE YOU COOL WITH THAT?

729
00:40:10,583 --> 00:40:12,500
- SOUNDS GOOD.

730
00:40:12,583 --> 00:40:14,500
- UNDERSTAND,
THE SNOW'S NOT A HANDICAP.

731
00:40:14,583 --> 00:40:15,583
IT'S YOUR BEST FRIEND.

732
00:40:15,666 --> 00:40:17,500
A TRAINING PARTNER LIKE
YOU'VE NOT HAD.

733
00:40:17,583 --> 00:40:19,666
RACERS DON'T GET
AN OFF SEASON, BROTHER.

734
00:40:22,666 --> 00:40:24,666
- ( tires squeal )

735
00:40:33,583 --> 00:40:36,166
- THESE STUDLESS TIRES,
THEY DON'T GRIP VERY WELL.

736
00:40:36,250 --> 00:40:38,500
- BUT STILL, THIS IS REALLY
GOOD TRAINING FOR YOU.

737
00:40:38,583 --> 00:40:41,416
LOOK, YOU SEE A CORNER,
YOU ATTACK IT.

738
00:40:41,500 --> 00:40:43,500
THAT'S THE VERY INSTINCT
OF A RACER.

739
00:40:47,041 --> 00:40:48,791
- WHOA.  CRAZY.

740
00:40:48,875 --> 00:40:50,541
I'VE NEVER SEEN
ANYBODY THAT FAST.

741
00:40:50,625 --> 00:40:52,041
- AND THAT WAS
A SIL-EIGHTY. 

742
00:40:52,125 --> 00:40:54,166
I MEAN, WHERE DID IT
EVEN COME FROM?

743
00:40:56,125 --> 00:40:58,166
- MAN, THAT DRIVER'S
GOT SOME MAD SKILLS.

744
00:41:01,875 --> 00:41:03,375
- HOW'S SHE HANDLING?

745
00:41:03,458 --> 00:41:05,458
- THESE ARE ALL ONE PATTERN,
MID-SPEED CORNERS

746
00:41:05,541 --> 00:41:06,666
WITH NO LIFE TO THEM.

747
00:41:06,750 --> 00:41:08,166
IT'S FREAKING BORING.

748
00:41:08,250 --> 00:41:10,583
I GUESS I'LL ALWAYS LIKE
USUI PASS THE BEST.

749
00:41:16,500 --> 00:41:18,375
- ( cellphone ringing )

750
00:41:18,458 --> 00:41:20,958
- Sayuki:
HELLO? OH HEY, SHINGO.

751
00:41:21,041 --> 00:41:22,208
WHAT'S GOING ON?

752
00:41:22,291 --> 00:41:23,791
WHAT?

753
00:41:23,875 --> 00:41:25,291
THOSE TWO HAVE BEEN
SEEING EACH OTHER? 

754
00:41:25,375 --> 00:41:27,250
SHE NEVER BOTHERED
TO TELL ME ABOUT IT.

755
00:41:27,333 --> 00:41:29,833
- THEY ARE.  AND HE'S ALL
JAZZED UP ABOUT IT.

756
00:41:29,916 --> 00:41:31,750
IN FACT, I THINK
THEY HAVE A DATE TODAY.

757
00:41:31,833 --> 00:41:33,583
- NO KIDDING.
GREAT FOR THEM.

758
00:41:33,666 --> 00:41:35,416
WELL, I HOPE THEY HAVE FUN.

759
00:41:35,500 --> 00:41:37,000
YEAH?

760
00:41:37,083 --> 00:41:38,416
YEAH, THAT'S NICE.

761
00:41:38,500 --> 00:41:41,583
WELL, CHRISTMAS IS
COMING UP PRETTY SOON.

762
00:41:41,666 --> 00:41:43,958
YEAH.
TALK TO YOU LATER.

763
00:41:46,083 --> 00:41:48,000
- ( phone beeps )

764
00:41:48,083 --> 00:41:50,916
- I WONDER IF ALL THOSE
YEARS WITHOUT A BOYFRIEND

765
00:41:51,000 --> 00:41:53,291
ARE FINALLY GONNA COME
TO AN END FOR MAKO?

766
00:41:56,666 --> 00:42:00,083
- I THINK THIS SW-20
IS A REALLY SWEET RIDE.

767
00:42:00,166 --> 00:42:01,833
- A TWO-SEATER'S FUN,

768
00:42:01,916 --> 00:42:03,333
BUT IT CAN KIND OF
CRAMP YOUR STYLE, 

769
00:42:03,416 --> 00:42:04,791
IF YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

770
00:42:04,875 --> 00:42:07,000
I THINK NEXT TIME,
I'M GOING TO HAVE TO BUY

771
00:42:07,083 --> 00:42:09,375
SOMETHING A WHOLE LOT MORE
PRACTICAL THAN THIS FOR SURE.

772
00:42:09,458 --> 00:42:12,541
A FOUR-WHEEL DRIVE SUV
MIGHT BE NICE.

773
00:42:12,625 --> 00:42:15,750
- WHY?  THAT DOESN'T MEAN
YOU'RE QUITTING RACING, DOES IT?

774
00:42:15,833 --> 00:42:17,708
- I THINK SO, YEAH.

775
00:42:24,791 --> 00:42:26,875
I DON'T WANT TO MAKE 
ANY EXCUSES ABOUT IT,

776
00:42:26,958 --> 00:42:29,958
BUT I THINK I'VE ALREADY
HAD MY FUN WITH RACING. 

777
00:42:30,041 --> 00:42:32,041
WHEN YOU'RE A BEGINNER,
YOU TRY YOUR HARDEST,

778
00:42:32,125 --> 00:42:33,791
YOU GIVE IT YOUR ALL.

779
00:42:33,875 --> 00:42:35,791
AND IT'S EXCITING 
TO GO FROM NOTHING

780
00:42:35,875 --> 00:42:38,708
TO A GUY THAT 
PEOPLE ADMIRE.

781
00:42:38,791 --> 00:42:40,291
BUT ONCE YOU REACH
A CERTAIN LEVEL,

782
00:42:40,375 --> 00:42:41,958
AND YOU KIND OF 
SEE YOUR LIMITS,

783
00:42:42,041 --> 00:42:43,625
YOU STOP SETTING
GOALS FOR YOURSELF.

784
00:42:43,708 --> 00:42:45,208
YOUR EAGERNESS SUBSIDES.

785
00:42:45,291 --> 00:42:47,791
IT'S JUST NOT
WHAT IT USED TO BE.

786
00:42:47,875 --> 00:42:50,625
- I GUESS THAT'S THE WAY
EVERYBODY SEEMS TO GROW

787
00:42:50,708 --> 00:42:52,166
OUT OF IT SOONER OR LATER.

788
00:42:52,250 --> 00:42:54,041
THAT'S HOW I DID.

789
00:42:54,125 --> 00:42:55,541
- I DON'T KNOW.

790
00:42:55,625 --> 00:42:57,208
I'M NOT SURE THAT
EVERYBODY'S GOALS

791
00:42:57,291 --> 00:42:59,583
CAN JUST UP AND VANISH
FROM THEIR LIVES THAT EASILY.

792
00:42:59,666 --> 00:43:01,041
- HUH?

793
00:43:01,125 --> 00:43:02,916
- AWHILE BACK,
THERE WAS THIS TIME

794
00:43:03,000 --> 00:43:04,583
WHEN I THOUGHT
AFTER THIS SUMMER

795
00:43:04,666 --> 00:43:06,250
I WAS GONNA
QUIT RACING TOO.

796
00:43:06,333 --> 00:43:07,666
BUT THEN I HAD
AN OPPORTUNITY

797
00:43:07,750 --> 00:43:09,666
TO WATCH THIS REALLY
HIGH LEVEL RACER

798
00:43:09,750 --> 00:43:11,666
AT THIS INTENSE COMPETITION.

799
00:43:11,750 --> 00:43:14,666
AFTER THAT I REALIZED HOW MUCH
MORE THERE IS TO THE CRAFT.

800
00:43:14,750 --> 00:43:17,666
- ( chuckles )

801
00:43:17,750 --> 00:43:20,666
I DON'T THINK I TAKE RACING
AS SERIOUSLY AS YOU DO.

802
00:43:20,750 --> 00:43:23,625
IT'S NOT LIKE I'M TRYING TO BE
A PRO OR ANYTHING LIKE THAT.

803
00:43:32,750 --> 00:43:34,375
- (  Mako gasps )

804
00:43:37,291 --> 00:43:39,291
- ( chuckles )

805
00:43:41,958 --> 00:43:44,125
- Miyahara: I DON'T EVEN KNOW
IF IT'S A POSSIBILITY,

806
00:43:44,208 --> 00:43:48,291
BUT I THINK IT'D BE COOL IF YOU
QUIT RACING ALONG WITH ME.

807
00:43:48,375 --> 00:43:49,625
- RACING A PASS IS ONE OF

808
00:43:49,708 --> 00:43:51,708
THE MOST DANGEROUS
THINGS IN THE WORLD.

809
00:43:51,791 --> 00:43:54,541
I DON'T THINK IT HAS TO DO
WITH YOU BEING A GIRL.

810
00:43:54,625 --> 00:43:56,291
IT'S JUST, I DON'T
WANT TO HAVE TO WORRY

811
00:43:56,375 --> 00:43:58,291
ABOUT YOU GETTING
INTO AN ACCIDENT.

812
00:43:58,375 --> 00:44:00,875
I KNOW, NO ONE CAN
TAKE AWAY YOUR RIGHT

813
00:44:00,958 --> 00:44:02,125
TO DO WHATEVER 
YOU WANT TO DO.

814
00:44:02,208 --> 00:44:03,250
THAT'S YOURS, OF COURSE.

815
00:44:03,333 --> 00:44:04,791
BUT IF I WAS YOUR BOYFRIEND,

816
00:44:04,875 --> 00:44:06,666
I WOULDN'T BE TOO CRAZY
ABOUT YOU KEEPING ON.

817
00:44:11,625 --> 00:44:14,750
IT'D WORRY ME SO MUCH
TO LET YOU RUN OFF EVERY NIGHT

818
00:44:14,833 --> 00:44:17,666
TO RACE SOME STRANGER WHO'S
GOT ONLY VICTORY IN HIS SIGHTS,

819
00:44:17,750 --> 00:44:19,791
AND NO CARE AS TO
HOW HE GETS IT.

820
00:44:19,875 --> 00:44:22,708
THERE'S SO MANY OTHER
FUN THINGS TO DO IN LIFE.

821
00:44:22,791 --> 00:44:24,791
THINGS YOU COULD BE
DOING WITH ME.

822
00:44:24,875 --> 00:44:26,750
I THINK IT MIGHT
SUIT YOU BETTER 

823
00:44:26,833 --> 00:44:29,416
TO PUT ON A FANCY DRESS AND
LET ME TAKE YOU OUT TO EAT.

824
00:44:29,500 --> 00:44:30,916
YOU'RE TOO PRETTY
TO LET IT WASTE

825
00:44:31,000 --> 00:44:32,708
BEHIND THE WHEEL OF A CAR.
- ( gasps )

826
00:44:47,375 --> 00:44:50,166
- I'M SERIOUS ABOUT EVERYTHING
I SAID TO YOU, MAKO.

827
00:44:50,250 --> 00:44:51,958
I'VE NEVER FELT
THIS WAY ABOUT ANYONE.

828
00:44:52,041 --> 00:44:52,916
YOU'RE THE FIRST.

829
00:44:55,666 --> 00:44:57,958
WILL YOU DO ME THE HONOR
OF BEING WITH ME?

830
00:45:22,708 --> 00:45:24,541
- I...

831
00:45:24,625 --> 00:45:28,125
I'M HONESTLY FLATTERED 
THAT YOU FEEL THIS WAY.

832
00:45:28,208 --> 00:45:30,208
I JUST DON'T KNOW
HOW I FEEL YET.

833
00:45:32,875 --> 00:45:34,791
I MEAN, WE-- WE JUST MET.

834
00:45:34,875 --> 00:45:37,000
WE HARDLY KNOW EACH OTHER.

835
00:45:37,083 --> 00:45:38,416
AND ALL OF THIS,

836
00:45:38,500 --> 00:45:40,750
IT JUST FEELS
KIND OF SUDDEN TO ME.

837
00:45:42,916 --> 00:45:44,833
- THAT'S OKAY, MAKO.

838
00:45:44,916 --> 00:45:47,250
I'M NOT ASKING FOR
AN ANSWER RIGHT NOW.

839
00:45:47,333 --> 00:45:48,750
HOW ABOUT YOU LET ME
TAKE YOU OUT AGAIN

840
00:45:48,833 --> 00:45:50,166
IN A WEEK OR SO.

841
00:45:50,250 --> 00:45:51,833
SAY MAYBE ON CHRISTMAS EVE?

842
00:45:51,916 --> 00:45:54,500
UNTIL THEN,
JUST GIVE IT SOME THOUGHT.

843
00:45:54,583 --> 00:45:56,458
NO RUSH.

844
00:46:06,791 --> 00:46:09,000
- ( humming "Jingle Bells" )

845
00:46:09,083 --> 00:46:10,708
AAH!

846
00:46:10,791 --> 00:46:12,333
- YOU'RE IN A GOOD
STINKIN' MOOD, DUMMY.

847
00:46:12,416 --> 00:46:13,791
YOU GOT SOME BIG
PLANS FOR CHRISTMAS

848
00:46:13,875 --> 00:46:14,958
YOU AIN'T TELLING US ABOUT?

849
00:46:15,041 --> 00:46:16,666
- I DON'T HAVE ANY PLANS.
I SWEAR I DON'T.

850
00:46:16,750 --> 00:46:19,375
- YOU DOING ANYTHING,
IKETANI?

851
00:46:19,458 --> 00:46:21,625
- OF COURSE NOT.
SPENDING ANOTHER NIGHT ALONE

852
00:46:21,708 --> 00:46:24,375
'CAUSE WE'RE THE LONELY DRIVERS.
ISN'T THAT RIGHT, ITSUKI?

853
00:46:24,458 --> 00:46:26,291
- COURSE IT'S SAD.
LET ME GO.

854
00:46:26,375 --> 00:46:30,083
- Yuuichi: WHAT A PATHETIC
BUNCH OF LOSERS.

855
00:46:39,625 --> 00:46:42,125
- WHAT'S WITH
THE SERIOUS FACE, GIRL?

856
00:46:42,208 --> 00:46:45,291
IT LOOKS LIKE SOMETHING'S
CHIPPING AWAY AT YOUR MIND.

857
00:46:45,375 --> 00:46:47,041
- I DON'T WANT
TO TALK ABOUT IT.

858
00:46:47,125 --> 00:46:48,916
NOT EVEN TO YOU,
SORRY.

859
00:46:49,000 --> 00:46:50,541
- THAT'S A BAD HABIT YOU GOT.

860
00:46:50,625 --> 00:46:52,708
KEEPING EVERYTHING THAT
BOTHERS YOU TO YOURSELF

861
00:46:52,791 --> 00:46:54,875
ALL THE TIME?
IT'LL TEAR YOU UP.

862
00:46:54,958 --> 00:46:56,708
- I JUST HAVE
A LOT ON MY MIND.

863
00:46:56,791 --> 00:46:58,541
I WOULDN'T EVEN
KNOW WHERE TO START.

864
00:46:58,625 --> 00:47:02,000
MOSTLY I KEEP WONDERING WHY I
EVEN BOTHER WITH RACING ANYMORE.

865
00:47:02,083 --> 00:47:03,500
- HMM?

866
00:47:03,583 --> 00:47:05,166
- STOP STARING AT ME.

867
00:47:05,250 --> 00:47:07,166
I KNOW THAT YOU AND I
USUALLY TRY TO AVOID 

868
00:47:07,250 --> 00:47:09,083
THIS KIND OF SERIOUS TALK.

869
00:47:09,166 --> 00:47:10,833
- I WANT TO BE
A BETTER RACER, I DO.

870
00:47:10,916 --> 00:47:13,333
BUT IT'S NOT LIKE
THAT'S ALL THAT DRIVES ME.

871
00:47:13,416 --> 00:47:16,625
THAT PROBABLY SOUNDS PRETTY
STRANGE TO YOU, DOESN'T IT?

872
00:47:16,708 --> 00:47:20,041
- NO, I DON'T THINK
IT SEEMS STRANGE AT ALL.

873
00:47:20,125 --> 00:47:23,000
HANG ON, DID SOMEBODY SAY
SOMETHING TO YOU? WHO WAS IT?

874
00:47:23,083 --> 00:47:26,083
HELL, I MEAN MAYBE YOU'RE
JUST TOO INNOCENT A GIRL.

875
00:47:26,166 --> 00:47:28,041
TOO EASILY INFLUENCED
BY OTHERS, YOU KNOW? 

876
00:47:31,583 --> 00:47:33,333
THE TWO OF US,
I MEAN, WE ARE WHO WE ARE

877
00:47:33,416 --> 00:47:35,208
NO MATTER WHAT
OTHER PEOPLE SAY.

878
00:47:35,291 --> 00:47:37,750
- ( gasps )

879
00:47:37,833 --> 00:47:39,166
( sighs )

880
00:47:39,250 --> 00:47:40,541
YEAH, I GUESS YOU'RE RIGHT.

881
00:48:09,041 --> 00:48:10,750
- ( car door opens )

882
00:48:18,041 --> 00:48:20,625
- IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

883
00:48:20,708 --> 00:48:22,833
- EVERYTHING'S FINE.

884
00:48:22,916 --> 00:48:25,000
BUT I'M SORRY TO HAVE TO
HAVE YOU COME OUT HERE

885
00:48:25,083 --> 00:48:27,041
ON CHRISTMAS EVE
OF ALL NIGHTS.

886
00:48:27,125 --> 00:48:31,333
- IT'S ALL GOOD.
REALLY JUST HAPPY TO SEE YOU.

887
00:48:31,416 --> 00:48:32,916
- I WANT YOU
TO DO SOMETHING.

888
00:48:33,000 --> 00:48:34,916
- WAIT.
I'M NOT RACING YOU.

889
00:48:35,000 --> 00:48:38,250
YOU'D HAVE TO BE CRAZY TO THINK
I'D EVEN CONSIDER DOING THAT.

890
00:48:38,333 --> 00:48:40,000
- WHICH IS WHY 
I'M NOT ASKING.

891
00:48:40,083 --> 00:48:41,583
I WANT YOU TO RIDE
NEXT TO ME

892
00:48:41,666 --> 00:48:42,875
WHEN I GO ON A RUN.

893
00:48:42,958 --> 00:48:43,958
- UH?

894
00:48:45,958 --> 00:48:47,416
- ( engine revs )

895
00:48:52,500 --> 00:48:55,000
- Mako: USUALLY IT'S SAYUKI
SITTING IN THE SEAT NEXT TO ME.

896
00:48:55,083 --> 00:48:57,958
THIS FEELS WAY DIFFERENT.
LIKE I'M CHEATING.

897
00:49:01,500 --> 00:49:02,958
RIGHT.
HOLD ONTO YOUR BOOTS.

898
00:49:19,250 --> 00:49:20,125
- ( gasps )

899
00:49:35,458 --> 00:49:37,041
- Miyahara:
DAMN, SHE'S GOOD.

900
00:49:37,125 --> 00:49:39,833
I HAD NO IDEA SHE COULD
ROCK IT LIKE THIS.

901
00:49:57,583 --> 00:50:00,083
YOU'RE WAY BETTER THAN
I THOUGHT YOU WERE, MAKO.

902
00:50:00,166 --> 00:50:02,666
WE ONLY HAVE A HANDFUL OF NIGHT
KIDS WHO CAN DRIVE LIKE THAT,

903
00:50:02,750 --> 00:50:04,583
AND YOU'D EVEN GIVE THEM
A RUN FOR THEIR MONEY.

904
00:50:04,666 --> 00:50:06,833
WHO KNOWS, YOU MIGHT EVEN
BE BETTER THAN TAKESHI

905
00:50:06,916 --> 00:50:09,416
AND SHINGO PUT TOGETHER.

906
00:50:09,500 --> 00:50:11,250
( sighs )

907
00:50:11,333 --> 00:50:12,833
DIDN'T TAKE ME LONG
TO FIGURE OUT

908
00:50:12,916 --> 00:50:14,250
WHY YOU HAD ME
RIDE WITH YOU TONIGHT.

909
00:50:14,333 --> 00:50:16,916
THAT WAS A SMART MOVE.

910
00:50:17,000 --> 00:50:20,250
I'M GUESSING THIS WOULD BE 
YOUR ANSWER TO MY QUESTION.

911
00:50:20,333 --> 00:50:22,750
- YEAH, I'M SORRY.

912
00:50:22,833 --> 00:50:23,916
BUT I THOUGHT ABOUT
IT PROBABLY MORE

913
00:50:24,000 --> 00:50:26,500
THAN I'VE THOUGHT
ABOUT ANYTHING.

914
00:50:26,583 --> 00:50:28,625
AT THE END OF THIS,
YOU MIGHT THINK

915
00:50:28,708 --> 00:50:30,541
I'M JUST SOME DUMB GIRL,

916
00:50:30,625 --> 00:50:32,541
BUT I CAN'T SHAKE
HOW BADLY I WANT TO RACE.

917
00:50:32,625 --> 00:50:33,958
IT'S PART OF WHO I AM.

918
00:50:39,166 --> 00:50:40,708
I'M A SIMPLE PERSON.

919
00:50:40,791 --> 00:50:42,708
I WANT TO KEEP CHASING
AFTER THE OTHER CARS

920
00:50:42,791 --> 00:50:46,125
IN FRONT OF ME THAT ARE
TRYING TO GET AWAY.

921
00:50:46,208 --> 00:50:48,125
AND I WANT TO DO IT,
EVEN IF I CAN'T--

922
00:50:48,208 --> 00:50:50,125
EVEN IF I CAN'T KEEP UP
WITH THEM, I DON'T CARE.

923
00:50:50,208 --> 00:50:52,083
I JUST WANT TO
KEEP MOVING.

924
00:50:52,166 --> 00:50:54,958
I'M SORRY ABOUT ALL THIS.

925
00:50:55,041 --> 00:50:56,791
HOW YOU TREATED ME
SINCE WE'VE MET

926
00:50:56,875 --> 00:51:00,541
HAS MADE ME FEEL
SO SPECIAL.

927
00:51:00,625 --> 00:51:01,708
- I UNDERSTAND.

928
00:51:04,625 --> 00:51:05,708
- BYE.

929
00:51:09,208 --> 00:51:11,583
- ( car door opens, closes )

930
00:51:11,666 --> 00:51:12,958
- ( engine starts )

931
00:51:21,666 --> 00:51:24,000
- Miyahara:
I DON'T KNOW WHO THEY ARE,

932
00:51:24,083 --> 00:51:27,583
BUT THE PEOPLE IN HER LIFE
THAT SHE CARES SO MUCH ABOUT

933
00:51:27,666 --> 00:51:29,583
DON'T KNOW HOW GOOD
THEY GOT IT.

934
00:51:29,666 --> 00:51:32,541
AND I COULDN'T BE
MORE JEALOUS OF THEM.

935
00:51:35,250 --> 00:51:37,125
- ( pop music playing )

936
00:51:37,208 --> 00:51:39,166
- WHY IS IT JUST
THE THREE OF US SITTING HERE?

937
00:51:39,250 --> 00:51:40,625
WHERE THE HELL IS TAKUMI?

938
00:51:40,708 --> 00:51:42,208
- MAYBE HE'S GOT
A BIG DATE TONIGHT.

939
00:51:42,291 --> 00:51:44,291
YOU NEVER KNOW.
- WHO CARES, GUYS?

940
00:51:44,375 --> 00:51:46,166
LET HIM HAVE HIS FUN.

941
00:51:46,250 --> 00:51:48,500
WHY DON'T WE JUST FOCUS
ON THE THREE OF US

942
00:51:48,583 --> 00:51:51,208
HAVING A BLAST!
YEAH!  SWEET.

943
00:51:51,291 --> 00:51:52,583
( laughing )

944
00:51:55,541 --> 00:51:57,416
- ( both sigh )
- MERRY CHRISTMAS!

945
00:52:01,250 --> 00:52:04,125
- ( theme song playing )

